    "attributes": {
        "action": "DVLA must refund partial road tax in full",
        "additional_details": "Why when taxing a car does the DVLA always win - surely in this day and age the DVLA could pro-rata the tax during the month?\r\n \r\nIf you tax on the last day of the month you are due to pay for the full month. If you sell a car on the first of the month, you don\u2019t get any of your tax refunded for that whole month.\r\n \r\nIn an ideal world you could sell a car on the last day of the month and buy on the first but this will never happen.\r\n \r\nI want the UK Government to change this system of always charging drivers the most amount of tax and to run a fair system.",
        "background": "STOP DVLA FROM OVERCHARGING ROAD TAX IN UK",
